TITLE: BM25 Formula for Ranking Code Search Results in Probe (Mathematical Expression)
DESCRIPTION: Presents the BM25 ranking formula applied by Probe to measure relevance between code blocks and queries. This formula accounts for term frequency, block length normalization, and saturation to enhance accuracy over basic TF-IDF. Inputs are block and query terms, constants k1 and b; output is a BM25 relevance score.
SOURCE: https://github.com/buger/probe/blob/main/site/search-reference.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
BM25(block, query) =  IDF(term) * (TF(term, block) * (k1 + 1)) / (TF(term, block) + k1 * (1 - b + b * (block_length / average_block_length)))
```

